   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sanitation and Hygiene Enhancement in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sanitation situation is very worst in the proposed working villages, 85% of the families don&apos;t have latrines, 3% families have proper sanitary latrines in rich households, rest 12% has unhygieni pit latrines. People used to do open defecations. Women suffer due to open defecation, as they have to attend open defecation during the night or in the early morning, which is a very indecent and shying issue for the women. Sun Flower intent to install 200 family latrines and aware of the community.</narrative>
  </description>
